<p>&nbsp;Within the database, users can browse over 1,400 Renewal skills, covering all job classes as well as monster and item-related abilities. The interface allows filtering between Renewal and Pre-Renewal systems, ensuring compatibility with different server types. Each skill entry provides structured information including its ID, name, maximum level, type, target, and a detailed description of its effects and requirements.</p>
<p>&nbsp;The database begins with fundamental abilities such as Basic Skill, which enables the use of core interface features like trading items and Zeny with other players. Combat-related skills include Sword Mastery, which increases damage when using one-handed swords and daggers, and Two-Handed Sword Mastery, which boosts damage for two-handed sword users but requires prior investment in Sword Mastery. Survivability skills such as Increase HP Recovery and Increase SP Recovery allow characters to regenerate health and mana over time while idle, scaling with maximum HP and SP respectively.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Offensive abilities play a major role in the database, with skills like Bash delivering strong physical attacks to a single enemy, and Magnum Break dealing fire-element area damage while pushing enemies back. Provoke acts as a debuff that lowers enemy defense while increasing their attack power, creating a risk-reward dynamic. Endure provides utility by allowing characters to continue attacking and moving even when taking damage, although it is less effective against magical attacks.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Magic-based skills are also extensively documented. Sight reveals hidden enemies within a certain radius, while Napalm Beat deals ghost-element damage to a target and surrounding area. Soul Strike builds on this by summoning holy spirits to inflict repeated ghost-element damage. Elemental bolt skills such as Fire Bolt, Cold Bolt, and Lightning Bolt deliver single-target magic damage of fire, water, and wind elements respectively, while advanced versions like Fire Ball and Thunder Storm expand these attacks into area-of-effect abilities.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Defensive and control-oriented magic includes Safety Wall, which creates a protective barrier, and Frost Driver, which can freeze enemies. Stone Curse applies a petrification effect at the cost of a gemstone, demonstrating how some skills require consumable items. Fire Wall creates a damaging barrier that also knocks enemies back, offering both offense and crowd control.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Support and utility skills are equally important. Ruwach and Sight both detect hidden enemies, while Teleport and Warp Portal allow fast travel across maps. Pneuma creates a protective zone that blocks ranged attacks, making it valuable in both PvE and PvP scenarios. Healing and buffing abilities such as Heal, Increase Agility, Blessing, and Angelus enhance survivability and performance by restoring HP or boosting stats like STR, INT, DEX, and movement speed. Debuffs like Decrease Agility reduce enemy effectiveness, while Cure removes negative status effects.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Merchant-related skills focus on economic advantages and inventory management. Enlarge Weight Limit increases carrying capacity, while Discount and Overcharge improve buying and selling prices with NPC shops. Pushcart enables additional storage through a cart system, and Vending allows players to open personal shops to sell items to others. Mammonite is a unique offensive skill that consumes Zeny to deal high damage, blending combat with economic resources.</p>
<p>&nbsp;Archer and Thief skill sets emphasize precision, mobility, and utility. Owl’s Eye and Vulture’s Eye increase dexterity, attack range, and accuracy for bow users, while Improve Concentration temporarily boosts agility and dexterity while revealing hidden enemies. Double Strafe and Arrow Shower provide strong ranged attacks, including area damage with knockback effects. Thief skills such as Double Attack increase the chance of hitting twice with daggers, Improve Dodge raises evasion, and Steal allows players to obtain items directly from enemies.</p>
